# GitHub Pages SPA redirect trick. When a deep link like /repo/about is requested,
# GitHub Pages serves this file because the path doesn't exist on disk. The script
# below rewrites the URL to /repo/?/about and redirects to the SPA root, where
# index.html's bootstrap script (in <head>) restores the original path before the
# router boots. Source: https://github.com/rafgraph/spa-github-pages
